{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_vrtx_01CgK8m49JdhY57ehadQdCth","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I now have all the information needed. Here's the complete implementation:\n\n---\n\n## Implementation\n\n### New file: `config/monitoring/prometheus-rule.yaml`\n\n```yaml\napiVersion: monitoring.coreos.com/v1\nkind: PrometheusRule\nmetadata:\n  labels:\n    app.kubernetes.io/name: prometheusrule\n    app.kubernetes.io/instance: multiarch-tuning-operator\n    app.kubernetes.io/component: monitoring\n    app.kubernetes.io/created-by: multiarch-tuning-operator\n    app.kubernetes.io/part-of: multiarch-tuning-operator\n    app.kubernetes.io/managed-by: kustomize\n  name: image-inspection-alerts\n  namespace: system\nspec:\n  groups:\n    - name: multiarch-tuning-operator.rules\n      rules:\n        - alert: MultiarchImageInspectionFailureRateCritical\n          expr: |\n            (\n              rate(mto_ppo_ctrl_failed_image_inspection_total[5m])\n              /\n              rate(mto_ppo_ctrl_processed_pods_total[5m])\n            ) > 0.05\n          for: 5m\n          labels:\n            severity: critical\n          annotations:\n            message: >-\n              Image inspection failure rate has exceeded 5% over the last 5 minutes.\n              Current failure rate is {{ $value | humanizePercentage }}.\n              This may indicate issues with image registry connectivity or\n              authentication that are preventing the multiarch tuning operator\n              from inspecting container images.\n```\n\n### New file: `config/monitoring/kustomization.yaml`\n\n```yaml\nresources:\n  - prometheus-rule.yaml\n```\n\n### Modified file: `config/default/kustomization.yaml`\n\nAdd `../monitoring` to the resources list:\n\n```yaml\napiVersion: kustomize.config.k8s.io/v1beta1\nkind: Kustomization\nresources:\n- ../crd\n- ../rbac\n- ../manager\n- ../webhook\n- ../monitoring\n```\n\n(Add `- ../monitoring` after `- ../webhook` on a new line.)\n\n---\n\n## Explanation\n\n**Metrics used:**\n- `mto_ppo_ctrl_failed_image_inspection_total` — counter incremented each time an image inspection fails (`controller.go:66`, used in `pod_model.go:502`)\n- `mto_ppo_ctrl_processed_pods_total` — counter of all pods processed by the pod placement controller (`controller.go:60`)\n\n**PromQL expression:** Computes the failure rate as `rate(failures[5m]) / rate(total[5m])` and fires when it exceeds 5% (`> 0.05`). The `for: 5m` clause ensures the condition must persist for 5 minutes before the alert fires, avoiding transient spikes.\n\n**Commands to run:**\n\n```bash\n# No make targets needed — the YAML is picked up by kustomize.\n# To verify the kustomize build includes the new resource:\ncd /Users/kpais/kpais-workspace/a_b_evals/repos/multiarch-tuning-operator-baseline\nmake kustomize\n./bin/kustomize build config/default\n```"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1297,"cache_read_input_tokens":40588,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1297,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":4},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"54bd4c1d-9b10-4eb8-90e5-55c024e4de42","uuid":"f68cf6a0-7d75-4daf-b5e7-ecec18dd62de","timestamp":"2026-07-16T13:47:41.151Z","request_id":"req_vrtx_011Cd5qhHDxqnaVaNWnYZ8ok"}
